Let \[f(x) =
\begin{cases}
3x + 5 &\text{if }x<-3, \\
7-4x&\text{if }x\ge -3.
\end{cases}
\]Find $f(-10)$.

For what ordered pair $(a,b)$ are there infinite solutions $(x,y)$ to the system \begin{align*}
2ax+2y&=b,\\
5x+y&=-3?
\end{align*}

Expand and simplify completely: \begin{align*}
x\left(x(1+x)+2x\right)-3(x^2-x+2)
\end{align*}

Find $a+b+c$, given that $x+y\neq -1$ and  \begin{align*}
ax+by+c&=x+7,\\
a+bx+cy&=2x+6y,\\
ay+b+cx&=4x+y.
\end{align*}
